components.naturalnumber

Class NaturalNumber2

  • java.lang.Object
    • components.naturalnumber.NaturalNumberCommon
      • components.naturalnumber.NaturalNumberSecondary
        • components.naturalnumber.NaturalNumber2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NaturalNumber, NaturalNumberKernel, Standard<NaturalNumber>, Comparable<NaturalNumber>

    public class NaturalNumber2
extends NaturalNumberSecondary
    NaturalNumber represented as a Stack<Integer> with implementations of primary methods.

    Execution-time performance of all methods implemented in this class is O(1), except the constructors from String (which is O(|s|)) and from NaturalNumber (which is O(log n)).

    Mathematical Definitions:
     HAS_ONLY_DIGITS (
   s: string of integer
  ): boolean satisfies
  if s = empty_string
   then HAS_ONLY_DIGITS (s) = true
   else for all a: string of integer, k: integer where (s = a * )
                   (HAS_ONLY_DIGITS (s) = (HAS_ONLY_DIGITS (a)  and  0 <= k < 10))
 
 IS_WELL_FORMED_RADIX_REPRESENTATION (
   s: string of integer
  ): boolean is
  s = empty_string  or
      there exists k: integer, a: string of integer 
       (s =  * a  and
        1 <= k < 10  and
        HAS_ONLY_DIGITS (a))
 
 NUMERICAL_VALUE (
   s: string of integer
  ): integer satisfies
  if s = empty_string
   then NUMERICAL_VALUE (s) = 0
   else for all a: string of integer, k: integer where (s = a * )
         (NUMERICAL_VALUE (s) = NUMERICAL_VALUE (a) * 10 + k)
    Representation Invariant (concrete invariant of $this):
     IS_WELL_FORMED_RADIX_REPRESENTATION (reverse ($this.digits))
    Abstraction Relation (interpretation mapping between $this and this):
     this = NUMERICAL_VALUE (reverse ($this.digits))
